menu SpIOpen Protocol Features

config SPIOPEN_BROKER_FRAME_POOL_SIZE_CONFIGURABLE
    bool "Support configurable (non-static) spiopen frame pools"
    default n
    help
        This allows a setting on the device to determine the size of the SpIOpen frame broker pool, but requires heap allocation of the frame pool at initialization.

config SPIOPEN_BROKER_MAX_SUBSCRIBER_COUNT
    int "Maximum number of simultaneous subscribers supported by the frame broker"
    range 4 128
    default 8
    help
        This options accepts integer values from 4 to 255. Each app and port is a subscriber

config SPIOPEN_BROKER_FRAME_POOL_MAX_CC_FRAMES
    int "Maximum number of CAN-CC Frames that can be configured in the CC Frame Pool"
    range 0 255
    default 32
    help
        The maximum (or fixed when non-configurable) number of CAN-CC frames available in the Frame Pool

config SPIOPEN_BROKER_FRAME_POOL_MAX_FD_FRAMES
    int "Maximum number of CAN-FD Frames that can be configured in the FD Frame Pool"
    range 0 255
    default 32
    help
        The maximum (or fixed when non-configurable) number of CAN-FD frames available in the Frame Pool

config SPIOPEN_BROKER_FRAME_POOL_MAX_XL_FRAMES
    int "Maximum number of CAN-XL Frames that can be configured in the XL Frame Pool"
    range 0 255
    default 32
    help
        The maximum (or fixed when non-configurable) number of CAN-XL frames available in the Frame Pool

config SPIOPEN_BROKER_MAILBOX_DEPTH_CONFIGURABLE
    bool "Support configurable (heap-backed) broker mailbox depth"
    default n
    help
        If enabled, mailbox queue storage and depth may be provided at runtime
        (typically from heap-backed initialization). If disabled, mailbox depth
        is fixed at compile time from SPIOPEN_BROKER_MAILBOX_MAX_DEPTH.

config SPIOPEN_BROKER_MAILBOX_MAX_DEPTH
    int "Maximum mailbox depth for broker mailbox queues"
    range 1 255
    default 32
    help
        The maximum (or fixed when non-configurable) queue depth for each broker
        mailbox. This setting applies to broker inbox and subscriber mailboxes.